window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>A former soldier turned PI solves crime in a world that's lost its magic in this brilliant sequel to actor Luke Arnold's debut </b><b><i>The Last Smile in Sunder City</i></b><b>. </b></p> <p>The name's Fetch Phillips - what do you need?&nbsp;</p> <p>Cover a Gnome with a crossbow while he does a dodgy deal? Sure.&nbsp;</p> <p>Find out who killed Lance Niles, the big-shot businessman who just arrived in town? I'll give it shot.&nbsp;</p> <p>Help an old-lady Elf track down her husband's murderer? That's right up my alley.&nbsp;</p> <p>What I don't do, because it's impossible, is search for a way to bring the goddamn magic back.&nbsp;</p> <p>Rumors got out about what happened with the Professor, so now people keep asking me to fix the world.&nbsp;</p> <p>But there's no magic in this story. Just dead friends, twisted miracles, and a secret machine made to deliver a single shot of murder.&nbsp;</p> <p><b>Welcome back to the streets of Sunder City, a darkly imagined world perfect for listeners of Ben Aaronovitch and Jim Butcher.</b></p>"; 
